  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      TB remains a health problem in France with about 5,000 new cases per year. Development of new
      screening tests is a priority for TB. The main objective of the study is to evaluate
      performances of innovative blood tests to identify active tuberculosis in adults patients
      living in low-prevalence country. Adult patients with possible TB from will be tested for the
      presence of antibodies directed against M. tuberculosis selected antigens. Positive and
      negative predictive values will be established based on TB culture results.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
